h3. Problem Definition

Currently, SD automation audit log only shown when we access using the URI below:
{code}
GET: {context path}/rest/servicedesk/automation/1/audit/ruleset/{id}

GET: {context path}/rest/servicedesk/automation/1/audit/execution/{id}
{code}

which is not feasible for admin user to identify the problem.

h3. Suggested Solution

It would be great if JIRA have an ability to shown this logs information in front end or append the logging in the service desk logs.

